I"{<div class="p">In Milton's verse I find my muse,</div>
<div class="p">A silent phantom hiding there.</div>
<div class="p">Homer's lines do spur me on</div>
<div class="p">To seek the truth that's just and fair.</div>
<p> </p>
<div class="p">In Dante's Hell I do abide</div>
<div class="p">If Shakespeare's plays are never near.</div>
<div class="p">In Dickens' work I always find</div>
<div class="p">A friend above the common tier.</div>
<p> </p>
<div class="p">To  Brontë I must surely flee</div>
<div class="p">When news of bad things come to pass</div>
<div class="p">Does touch my soul and shatter thus</div>
<div class="p">That pane of fragile, frosted glass.</div>
<p> </p>
<div class="p">To Melville I shall pledge my time,</div>
<div class="p">Spear for him a whale at sea,</div>
<div class="p">To be rewarded for my time</div>
<div class="p">With days of solemn ecstasy.</div>
